                            <comment id="17371156" author="bereng" created="Tue, 29 Jun 2021 06:34:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is just a plain timeout. The traceback doesn&apos;t pin down which exact test case failed but there is only one candidate &lt;tt&gt;testMessageMatching&lt;/tt&gt; as it&apos;s the only one issuing a &lt;tt&gt;SELECT&lt;/tt&gt; that shouldn&apos;t fail. Seems like a reasonable guess despite the other test case with &lt;tt&gt;SELECT&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It can be reproduced by placing a breakpoint &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/bereng/cassandra/blob/CASSANDRA-16771-4.0.0/src/java/org/apache/cassandra/service/reads/ReadCallback.java#L101&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;. The solution is to raise the timeout for this test and now it survives a 1K CI run.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
